<font color="#FF0000">AGENT ORANGE &amp; MUSROOM CLOUDS</font><br>
<tt>Mon Oct  6 18:33:12 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br><br>
Art;<br>
Just take a good straight shot of Agent Orange, used to come in the 12 oz bottle size in Nam for us to drink.  but we also bought it in the fifty gallon drum size for weekend ecelebration from Mamma Sanh.<br><br>
Heck, SW<br>
I used to see the type of show you described almost everyday.<br>
LA traffic, drive-by-shootings, earthquakes, but I think Nam was safer. Used to drive into LA to work the morning shift in Watts, when I got off the freeway I would reach over and take out my 9mm, roll down the window and listen to the sounds.  AK47's going off, people screaming, siren blurring, police chopper with search light speedily flying overhead. <br>
By the time I got to the station I would have passed two or three squad cars with their red lights on and at the stations parking lot an assembly resembling a military staging area as everyone would be lock and loading, checking their shotguns, gas masks, etc. Guess I never had time to disassociate myself from the war, just got paid a little more and didn't have the luxury off calling in artillery, napalm or naval gunfire.<br><br>
Earthquakes are a different, can you get PTSD from Earthquakes in California?<br>
I have never understood how so many people that don't practice their religious convictions all managed to somehow always coordinate their prayer time to correspond to the beginning of earthquakes in this area.<br><br>
Took a break this weekend, haven't gone to see a flick in quite awhile so I took my wife out to see three of them.  Peacemaker, the Edge and U-Turn. The Edge was about the best, you guys would enjoy it. No meaningful dialog in Peacemaker reminded me of the Corps, improvise as you go along, as far as U-Turn I should have done that at the door. Its not often I can just relax like that, guess I needed it.<br><br>
Missing Tang 2,<br>
Entrenching tool? guns never carried such a thing. Lt once asked me if I had an E2, I told him no Sir, I'm a machine gunner. Never needed one after that. There was always a soft grave site we could dig into if things got bad. Besides once we did that we could always count that body as another confirmed kill. <br><br>
Finally recieved combat boots with steel toes in them a week before I left Nam, still have them. <br><br>
Can't get over SW being just plain Bob. we would have given you a proper name in Nam, like BoBo or Re-up something with a little dignity. <br><br>

